Net-SNMP-Poller

Net::SNMP::Poller runs non-blocking SNMP queries against hostname / OID
combination that you provide (along with session / request information) and
return the results in a data structure.

PREREQUISITES

The following modules are required by Net::OAuth::Yahoo:
    Net::SNMP

Also, your target nodes need to have snmpd configured and running so that
the queries would succeed.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Net::SNMP::Poller

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Net-SNMP-Poller

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Net-SNMP-Poller

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Net-SNMP-Poller

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Net-SNMP-Poller/


